{"id":"1210.3807","submitter":"Rui Palma","authors":"Rui Palma","title":"Quasi-symmetric group algebras and C*-completions of Hecke algebras","comments":"20 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.OA math.FA math.GR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show that for a Hecke pair $(G, \\Gamma)$ the $C^*$-completions $C^*(L^1(G,\n\\Gamma))$ and $pC^*(\\bar{G})p$ of its Hecke algebra coincide whenever the group\nalgebra $L^1(\\bar{G})$ satisfies a spectral property which we call\n\"quasi-symmetry\", a property that is satisfied by all Hermitian groups and all\ngroups with subexponential growth. We generalize in this way a result of\nKaliszewski, Landstad and Quigg. Combining this result with our earlier results\nand a theorem of Tzanev we establish that the full Hecke $C^*$-algebra exists\nand coincides with the reduced one for several classes of Hecke pairs,\nparticularly all Hecke pairs $(G, \\Gamma)$ where $G$ is nilpotent group. As a\nconsequence, the category equivalence studied by Hall holds for all such Hecke\npairs. We also show that the completions $C^*(L^1(G, \\Gamma))$ and\n$pC^*(\\bar{G})p$ do not always coincide, with the Hecke pair\n$(SL_2(\\mathbb{Q}_q), SL_2(\\mathbb{Z}_q))$ providing one such example.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 14 Oct 2012 16:16:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-10-16"}
