llisional segments. Each hydrogenoid\nmodel predicts a discrete set of finitely measured neighbourhoods of orbits\nwith vanishing far-fields at the correct atomic magnitude and in quantitative\nand qualitative agreement with experiment and quantum mechanics, i.e., the\nspacings between consecutive discrete angular momenta agree with Planck's\nconstant within thirty-percent, while orbital frequencies agree with a\ncorresponding spectroscopic line within a few percent.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 14 Oct 2012 22:03:12 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Wed, 20 Feb 2013 12:28:33 GMT"},{"version":"v11","created":"Fri, 1 Mar 2013 22:36:26 GMT"},{"version":"v12","created":"Sun, 17 Mar 2013 18:21:55 GMT"},{"version":"v13","created":"Tue, 26 Mar 2013 22:57:16 GMT"},{"version":"v14","created":"Tue, 2 Apr 2013 16:48:39 GMT"},{"version":"v15","created":"Mon, 8 Apr 2013 19:54:56 GMT"},{"version":"v16","created":"Mon, 29 Apr 2013 01:25:27 GMT"},{"version":"v17","created":"Mon, 13 May 2013 17:38:20 GMT"},{"version":"v18","created":"Tue, 14 May 2013 00:16:18 GMT"},{"version":"v19","created":"Mon, 27 May 2013 14:36:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Oct 2012 21:01:51 GMT"},{"version":"v20","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2013 16:04:02 GMT"},{"version":"v21","created":"Sat, 27 Jul 2013 13:59:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 29 Oct 2012 21:55:57 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 6 Nov 2012 16:52:36 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 11 Nov 2012 20:05:15 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 30 Nov 2012 13:31:59 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Wed, 26 Dec 2012 19:54:13 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Tue, 29 Jan 2013 00:07:45 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Sun, 10 Feb 2013 20:51:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-07-30"}
